d nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 6:09:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=531.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Idiots in Highpass /sigh</span><hr size=1> I've been told repeatedly, on more than one server, that Highpass Hold is a FFA (free-for-all) zone, which apparently is supposed to mean that neither the Play Nice Policy nor civilised behaviour apply (nor enlightened self-interest neither, for that matter).<br><br>Even here on Firiona Vie, I was once in a group that insisted on leaving the gnolls (where we were doing just fine) to go over and try to kill-steal the orc camp from another group.  The reason being that somebody in the orc camp had offended somebody in my group the other day, and now he wanted revenge.  I couldn't talk them out of it, so I had to disband,as I didn't want my name (or my guild's) being associated with that kind of behaviour.  I went back to the gnolls and solod them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukolanistormynytes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KolaniStormynytes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 12:36:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=531.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Idiots in Highpass /sigh</span><hr size=1> I try to avoid Highpass completely. Even if I have to trudge through Da Swamp to do so. In my experience, Highpass is one of those &quot;easy-levelling&quot; zones like LOIO that everyone and their dog levels their characters up in. I make it a point to avoid those zones.<br><br>Then again, I'm currently killing Hill Giants in Rathe Mountains. <p>Kolani - <center><A Href="http://www.geocities.com/kelethinlegions" target="new"><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/kelelegions/kolanibanner.jpg" border="0"></A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umrgoodkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mr Goodkin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 12:59:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=531.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Idiots in Highpass /sigh</span><hr size=1> Regarding Highpass, it is an easy level zone if you can get a group.  I avoid zones like LOIO and Oasis due to crowds and drops (on this server exp isn't enough for me, need skins, silk or coin drops more than exp).  However, I have always likes HHP and HHK because they are outposts in the mountains.  I like the way the zones look, especially HHP.  <br><br>I may try and go there but for reasons different than most.  I like the story line and graphics there.  Wish they would do something with the hidden rooms in HHK.  Besides, small bronze drops in HHK. <p>May Brell shine the light in your eyes ~ <BR> Goody <BR> Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=531.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=531.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/cla